info.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 30 at 6:04PM PST until February 01 at 4:00AM PST by NWS Monterey
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 4 AM WEDNESDAY TO 4 AM PST THURSDAY... * WHAT...Southeast winds 15 to 25 mph with gusts up to 45 mph expected. * WHERE...Southern Salinas Valley, Arroyo Seco, and Lake San Antonio and Northern Salinas Valley, Hollister Valley, and Carmel Valley. * WHEN...From 4 AM Wednesday to 4 AM PST Thursday. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result.
info.instruction: Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
